!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

feeling /ˈfiːlɪŋ/

(feelings) 

1. N-COUNT A feeling is an emotion, such as anger or happiness. 情绪 

例： It gave me a feeling of satisfaction. 它给了我一种满足感。 

例： He was unable to contain his own destructive feelings. 他无法克制自己的消极情绪。 

2. N-COUNT If you have a feeling of hunger, tiredness, or other physical sensation, you experience it. 感觉 

例： I also had a strange feeling in my neck. 我的脖子也有一种奇怪的感觉。 

例： Focus on the feeling of relaxation. 专注于放松的感觉。 

3. N-COUNT If you have a feeling that something is the case or that something is going to happen, you think that is probably the case or that it is probably going to happen. 预感 

例： I have a feeling that everything will be all right. 我有种预感一切都会好起来的。 

4. N-PLURAL Your feelings about something are the things that you think and feel about it, or your attitude toward it. 看法; 态度 

例： She has strong feelings about the alleged growth in violence against female officers. 她对据称的女性军官遭遇暴力事件的增多有强烈的看法。 

例： I think that sums up the feelings of most discerning and intelligent Indians. 我认为那综合了最有眼力和智慧的印第安人的观点。 

5. N-PLURAL When you refer to someone's feelings , you are talking about the things that might embarrass, offend, or upset them. For example, if you hurt someone's feelings , you upset them by something that you say or do. 感情 

例： He was afraid of hurting my feelings. 他害怕伤我的感情。 

6. N-UNCOUNT Feeling is a way of thinking and reacting to things which is emotional and not planned rather than logical and practical. 感情用事 

例： He was prompted to a rare outburst of feeling. 他被激发而感情用事，这很少见。 

7. N-UNCOUNT Feeling for someone is love, affection, sympathy, or concern for them. (爱、关切、同情等) 感情 

例： Thomas never lost his feeling for Harriet. 托马斯从未失去对哈丽雅特的感情。 

8. N-UNCOUNT Feeling in part of your body is the ability to experience the sense of touch in this part of the body. 知觉 

例： After the accident he had no feeling in his legs. 事故之后他的双腿失去了知觉。 

9. N-UNCOUNT Feeling is used to refer to a general opinion that a group of people has about something. (一群人的) 观点 

例： There is still some feeling in the art world that the market for such works may be declining. 艺术界仍存在一种看法，认为这种作品的市场前景暗淡。 

10. N-SING If you have a feeling of being in a particular situation, you feel that you are in that situation. (处于某种处境的) 感觉 

例： I had the terrible feeling of being left behind to bring up the baby while he had fun. 我有种可怕的感觉，觉得自己被扔下抚养孩子，而他却在享乐。 

11. N-SING If something such as a place or book creates a particular kind of feeling , it creates a particular kind of atmosphere. 气氛 

例： That's what we tried to portray in the book, this feeling of opulence and grandeur. 那正是我们想要在这本书里所要营造的，那种繁荣且伟大的气氛。 

12.  →  see also feel 

13. PHRASE Bad feeling or ill feeling is bitterness or anger which exists between people, for example, after they have had an argument. 敌意 

例： There's been some bad feeling between the two families. 这两个家族之间互有敌意。 

14. PHRASE Hard feelings are feelings of anger or bitterness toward someone who you have had an argument with or who has upset you. If you say ' no hard feelings ,' you are making an agreement with someone not to be angry or bitter about something. 芥蒂 

例： I don't want any hard feelings between our companies. 我不希望我们两家公司之间有任何芥蒂。

